---
description: BOTSPEAK — write AI-facing docs in compressed symbol+alias notation, not prose
alwaysApply: true
---

# BOTSPEAK [ALWAYS]

[NEW-CHAT] this rule = active · all NEW AI-facing docs (rules · skills · CLAUDE.md · AGENTS.md · memory · handoffs) → write in BOTSPEAK
[NEW-CHAT] EXISTING docs in repo → only refactor when user explicitly asks
[ALWAYS] user-facing content (questions · choices · errors · explanations to user) → full human prose · zero BOTSPEAK

@defs
  ST = symbol-table
  PT = phase-tag
  AL = alias-block
@end

# symbols (apply without re-defining)
🔴 = block/never · ✅ = allowed · ⚠️ = warn · → = causes · · = AND · / = OR · ≠ = not-equal · = = defined-as

# phase tags (every block gets one)
[NEW-CHAT] [ALWAYS] [ON-TRIGGER] [REFERENCE] [HANDOFF]

# the killer feature
identifiers used ≥3× in same doc → put in @defs block at top · use short form everywhere after
mnemonic letters preferred: E (establishment) · S (settings) · MV (materialized-view)
section-scope @defs for very long docs

# write order for new AI-facing docs
1. inventory: invariants · triggers · constraints · repeated terms
2. build @defs for repeated terms (≥3× use)
3. tag every block with PT
4. compress prose: drop articles · filler · hedging · throat-clearing
5. keep: constraints · invariants · cause chains · exact values
6. long doc (>10 lines) → wrap in XML: <context> <defs> <rules> <reference>

# skills available (load when triggered)
/botspeak           -> compress an existing doc into BOTSPEAK
/capture-botspeak   -> capture messy chat -> focused BOTSPEAK doc
/translate-botspeak -> render BOTSPEAK -> human prose for audit/review

# reference
[REFERENCE] SPEC.md = full grammar · examples/ = before-after pairs

# the inviolable rule
[ALWAYS] user reads it → prose · agent reads it → BOTSPEAK
